article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Jeremiah Quigley scored 19 points as Iona beat Siena 70-51 on Friday night. Quigley finished 8 of 12 from the field for the Gaels (9-10, 4-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Greg Gordon added 15 points while going 7 of 17 (1 for 4 from 3-point range), and also had 12 rebounds. Zek Tekin led the Saints (3-16, 2-6) in scoring, finishing with 17 points and two steals. Bralyn Smith added nine points for Siena. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
